My visit to this establishment stems from a YouTube channel known as FND Films, a group that’s been making short (mostly comedic) films for over a decade now. Back in the early 2010’s this particular channel would upload vlogs at times titled as “FND Dailes.”  They used to live on the north side of Chicago and would frequent Redmond’s for their “wing nights.” This is a creative, hilarious, and genuine group of guys whose content I’ve enjoyed since I was in high school. The reason for this digression of an intro stems from an FND Daily on YouTube titled Wing Night. The wings that they showed in this particular vlog were from Redmond’s Ale House and they looked absolutely delicious. I first watched this daily back in 2010. Years later, I can finally confirm that after nearly a decade of craving these traditional bone-in wings that they live up to the hype that this video had set up for them. Not only were the wings delicious, they came out literally within 10 minutes of me ordering them, which I was impressed by because the location was pretty busy the night I went. While it’s a Vikings fan’s bar, it was definitely a great, laid-back sports bar with a great and affordable selection of drinks and food. I absolutely recommend this spot (even if you’re a hardcore Bears fan like me). I loved it and will absolutely stop by again. Great environment, great food, great drinks, great night. Shout out to FND Films, check them out on YouTube; their content is slept on. Also shout out to Redmond’s Ale House. I loved it.

Dive bar near Wrigley Field but gets five stars from me since I am a hardcore Vikings fan and Redmonds is the bar where all Vikings fans can congregate and watch every game even preseason. It’s packed with Vikings fans for every game. Also they have the Minnesota wild hockey games on as well as the sound on lots  of tvs.  If you are in Minnesota sports fan or a transplant it’s a fun place to hang out. I can’t imagine going here for any other reason besides watching sports.  During hockey and football games they have some pretty amazing drink specials.  As far as food is concerned, I tried the chicken wings and they were meh.  It’s not really a place for you to go to eat. Drink, Hang out with fellow Minnesotans, and commiserate about the Wild and the Vikes. Skol.

Came here after a rehearsal with my improv group. Their deals are ridiculously good with 50 cent wings on Thursdays and $5 bud light pitchers, I haven't seen that anywhere else in Wrigley, or even Chicago. This was All good, but our server came to us and asked us if we were ready to order immediately after sitting down. we politely declined and asked for a menu. the place was empty mind you. She returned with 1 for our party of 5 and repeated her question. A few friends had questions about the wing deals which were interrupted by her spurting off a spiel she says to everyone. we eventually got her to warm up to us. but it was too much. She proceeded to complain about working there and customers of color. It was extremely uncomfortable and I will not return as long as she is there. I've worked restaurants most of my life and if I had seen an employee act like that I would make sure they wouldn't ever work in a service role nearby ever again.

I had the same experience with a rude server. We had a group of people there and some us went outside to smoke. When we came back our beers were gone. The server claimed we were stocking up on beers. I told her no because some of us were at the table while others were smoking. She still took the beers. I walked up to her and asked I she could get me a manager, she rolled her eyes and picked up the phone, then hung up and that was it. Then I tracked down the manager and he was just as rude as her. Said the same thing and sided with the server. Clearly they care more about their staff then the customers. I walked out and I will never go back again! I have never been treated so rudely at a bar, especially by a manager. The owner needs to reconsider who they have working for them or they will be outta business!
